184
00:10:21.184 --> 00:10:22.344
What percentage was it, just quickly?

185
00:10:22.624 --> 00:10:22.773
Sorry?

186
00:10:22.804 --> 00:10:24.213
What percentage was allowed to carry?

187
00:10:24.244 --> 00:10:27.484
10. The current provisions allow up to 10%.

188
00:10:27.544 --> 00:10:31.524
So the lesser of under catch or 10%, whichever is the lesser.

189
00:10:33.144 --> 00:10:36.924
So we do think there are circumstances where larger

190
00:10:36.964 --> 00:10:40.464
amounts should be considered. We've talked about the economic stress

191
00:10:40.474 --> 00:10:44.424
that not being able to take ACE can cause for people who've paid

192
00:10:44.484 --> 00:10:48.474
a significant cost for it and, for example, can't get an economic

193
00:10:48.784 --> 00:10:51.304
return. I mean, the fuel crisis is one of those things.

194
00:10:51.364 --> 00:10:53.274
If diesel price were to go beyond

195
00:10:54.104 --> 00:10:57.024
$4 or $5, clearly a lot of boats would need to tie up.

196
00:10:57.204 --> 00:11:01.184
It's got nothing to do with the sustainability of the fishery, but it

197
00:11:01.224 --> 00:11:04.904
is a kind of a self-mechanism to allow for...

198
00:11:04.924 --> 00:11:07.484
It doesn't involve the government and compensating or assistance.

199
00:11:07.854 --> 00:11:11.404
It just allows those catching rights from year one to be carried forward into year

200
00:11:11.464 --> 00:11:11.644
two.

201
00:11:11.884 --> 00:11:14.214
And Gabrielle, can you just quickly talk about why you didn't do it in Gabrielle?

202
00:11:14.344 --> 00:11:15.684
So Gabrielle's,

